Egypt Stocks: Lecico Egypt and Talaat Moustafa Group Were Active

-- B y   A h m e d   A .   N a m a t a l l a
-- 
2011-06-21T13:47:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-21/egypt-stocks-juhayna-food-industries-lecico-egypt-are-active.html
Egypt’s benchmark  EGX 30 Index (EGX30) 
retreated for a second day, dropping 0.9 percent to 5,529.24 at
the 2:30 p.m. close in Cairo, the lowest level in more than a
week.  The following shares rose or fell in Cairo. Symbols are in
parentheses.  Lecico Egypt SAE (LCSW)   gained for the first time in
four days, increasing 1.2 percent to 15.20 Egyptian pounds. The
Alexandria, Egypt-based maker of sanitary ware and tiles will
distribute one free share for every three held on July 7 to
shareholders as of July 6. That will raise the company’s capital
to 400 million Egyptian pounds ($67 million) from 300 million
pounds.  Talaat Moustafa Group (TMGH)  Holding climbed 2.2 percent
to 5.15 pounds, the highest in almost three months. An advisory
panel of judges recommended  Egypt ’s biggest publicly traded
property developer keep the land it purchased from the
government for its Madinaty project. Judge Hassan Abdel Aziz
delayed ruling in the case until Oct. 4, saying the court needed
time to study the panel’s report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ahmed A Namatalla in Cairo at 
 anamatalla@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net  